# {{.ProjectName}}

TypeScript + Next.js {{.NextVersion}} on Node {{.NodeVersion}}, managed with {{.PackageManager}}.

## Architecture

```
src/
├── app/          # App Router — layouts, pages, route handlers
├── components/   # React components (ui/ for primitives, features/ for domain)
├── lib/          # Shared utilities, constants, client-side helpers
├── server/       # Server-only code: actions, data fetching, auth
└── types/        # Shared TypeScript type definitions
```

- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when you need interactivity or browser APIs
- Colocate server actions in `src/server/actions/` — never define actions inline in components
- Data fetching happens in Server Components or server actions, never in client components directly

## Commands

```bash
{{.PackageManager}} dev          # Start development server
{{.PackageManager}} build        # Production build
{{.PackageManager}} start        # Start production server
{{.PackageManager}} lint         # Run ESLint
{{.PackageManager}} test         # Run tests (Vitest)
{{.PackageManager}} test --watch # Run tests in watch mode
```

## Key Decisions

- **RSC-first**: Default to Server Components. Only use client components for state, effects, or event handlers.
- **Validation**: Use Zod for all runtime validation — form inputs, API responses, env vars
- **Imports**: Use absolute imports via `@/` prefix (maps to `src/`). Never use relative imports that go up more than one level.
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS only. No CSS modules, styled-components, or inline style objects.
- **State management**: Use React's built-in state (`useState`, `useReducer`, `useContext`). No Redux or Zustand unless the data problem genuinely demands it.
- **Forms**: Use server actions with `useActionState` for form submissions. Validate with Zod on both client and server.
